{"serial": "08008", "department_serial": 2, "code": "SC0003", "class": "I", "name": {"en": "Student Service-Learning", "ch": "服務學習課程"}, "notice": {"en": "", "ch": "1.此為選課用時段，實際上課時間將由課程助教另行通知。本課程本著連結在地社區的服務學習精神，同時以環境與生態維護為主軸規畫，藉以提升同學關懷在地與服務社會之公民素養。 2.因課程考量，本課程僅收地科系學生。"}, "instructor": {"en": ["Chan, Chung-Han"], "ch": ["詹忠翰"]}, "credits": 0, "time_loc": [{"time": {"week": 6, "session": ["3", "4"]}, "loc": {"building": "S", "room": "112"}}], "isRequired": true, "isFullSem": false, "MaxStu": -1, "department": {"ch": "學務處-服務學習發展中心", "en": "Division of Student Affairs-Center for Service Learning"}, "system": {"ch": "學士班", "en": "Undergraduate Programme"}, "language": {"ch": "國語", "en": "Chinese"}, "card": {"ch": "不使用", "en": "None"}, "assigned": 0, "selected": 55, "remark": {"ch": "1.此為選課用時段，實際上課時間將由課程助教另行通知。本課程本著連結在地社區的服務學習精神，同時以環境與生態維護為主軸規畫，藉以提升同學關懷在地與服務社會之公民素養。 2.因課程考量，本課程僅收地科系學生。", "en": ""}, "goal": {"ch": "學生進入大學就讀，不僅是追求學識的真理，如何運用自身的專業知識善盡社會責任，亦是一門重要的課題。本課程設計希望透過「服務」，能讓學生察覺日常生活中的在地問題，並且運用科學知識鏈結在地化服務，深度了解自身周遭所面臨的公共議題，進而著手改善、解決問題。", "en": "College students not only pursuing the truth of knowledge, but also learn how to use their professional knowledge to fulfill their social responsibilities, which is also an important topic in the education of a university. This course hopes students can perceive local problems in their daily lives and use scientific knowledge to link localized services to gain in-depth understanding of public issues facing them around them through “services“, so as to improve and solve problems."}, "outline": {"ch": "***因疫情關係，實際授課內容或適當調整***(一)準備（專業技能或觀念強化之課程安排）本課程擬於學期初介紹桃園市海岸現存石滬群之分布，並邀請桃園石滬協會至課堂上分享新屋百年石滬之歷史及文化意義，及目前面臨的現況危機與環境影響層面。(二)服務（社會實踐方案或服務計畫之安排）配合本校USR「桃海三生」計畫，本課程將邀請學生前往桃園市新屋區海岸線之石滬區域，協助進行特定範圍大小的石滬現地勘查與動手協助修復。藉由實地參訪與實際動手的修滬作業，以更深入瞭解先人利用智慧與地球科學相關知識，而與大自然共榮共存的歷史背景。(三)反思（引導學生反思並紀錄各項準備過程或服務過程之課程活動）透過本活動瞭解過去先人的生活方式，但隨著科技的發展，這種緩慢且效率不彰的捕魚方式似乎已沒有存在的必要？然而在近年人類過度捕撈漁獲與消耗大自然資源的聲音甚囂塵上，是否可藉由瞭解過去與現代人類取用自然資源的差異性，來反省並尋求最好的與大自然共存的方式。 (四)慶賀（分享、感恩回饋、評量結果或成果發表之安排）於期末安排同學們分組上臺分享成果，利用團體分組討論的方式，得以訓練學生多元蒐集資料的能力、深度認識了解日常生活的環境議題，並學習解決問題。而在面臨團體中的意見分歧時，亦能學習組織與溝通能力並客觀包容多元觀點。", "en": "***Due to the Covid-19 epidemic situation, the content of class may be adjusted appropriately***1. Preparation (course arrangement for strengthening professional skills or concepts)This course intends to introduce the stone fish weir in coastal line of the Taoyuan City, and invite association of the stone fish weir of Taoyuan to sharing the historical and cultural background of the stone fish weir in Hsing-Wu, as well as the current crisis and environmental impact.2. Service (arrangement of social practice or service plan)In conjunction with NCU’s “TaoCoast Project“, this course will invite students to go to the stone fish weir in the coastline in Hsing-Wu to visit and fix the stone fish weir. Through the in-situ visits and hands-on construction work, we can gain a deeper understanding of the historical background of the ancestors‘ wisdom and knowledge related to earth science to co-exist with nature.3. Rumination (guide students to reflect on and record various preparation processes or service process curriculum activities)Learn the way of life from our ancestors through this activity. Someone maybe think the slow and inefficient approach of fishing seems unnecessary in the modern world. However, in recent years, the voices of human overfishing and depletion of large natural resources have become louder. Is it possible to introspect and seek the best way to coexist with nature by understanding the differences between the past and the modern human beings‘ use of natural resources?"}, "textbook": {"ch": "無", "en": "NA"}, "selfCompiledRate": {"ch": "0", "en": "0"}, "instructMethod": {"ch": "講授\n研討\n實習/實驗", "en": ["Lecture", "Seminar", "Practical Training Lab"]}, "gradMethod": {"ch": "平時成績(50％)、實習或報告成績(50％)", "en": "General Performance (50％)、Final Report (50％)"}, "officeHour": {"ch": "星期三12:00~13:00、 星期四12:00~13:00", "en": "Wed. 12:00~13:00、Thu 12:00~13:00"}, "teachWeeks": {"ch": "18", "en": "18"}, "flexDiscription": {"ch": "", "en": ""}, "domain": {"ch": "服務學習課程", "en": "服務學習課程"}, "map": {"ch": [{"competencies": "增進學生對服務學習內涵的認知", "rating": "(4)高", "assesments": ["實作/實驗", "出席/課堂表現"]}, {"competencies": "提升學習與服務成效。", "rating": "(4)高", "assesments": ["實作/實驗", "出席/課堂表現"]}, {"competencies": "影響學生「服務學習的態度」與「行為意願」。", "rating": "(4)高", "assesments": ["實作/實驗", "出席/課堂表現"]}], "en": [{"competencies": "", "rating": "(4)High", "assesments": ["Practices/Experiments", "Attendance/Performance"]}, {"competencies": "", "rating": "(4)High", "assesments": ["Practices/Experiments", "Attendance/Performance"]}, {"competencies": "", "rating": "(4)High", "assesments": ["Practices/Experiments", "Attendance/Performance"]}]}, "assignCriteria": {"ch": ["系所:限地球科學學系。年級:限一年級。", "系所:限地球科學學系。"], "en": ["Department:Department of Geophysics only.Year:First Year only.", "Department:Department of Geophysics only."]}, "preselecStu": 0, "stuGender": {"male": 41, "Female": 14}, "stuGrade": {"doctor": {}, "master": {}, "bachelor": {"2": 1, "1": 54}}, "stus": [{"serial": "1", "stunum": "11*******", "department": "地球科學學系", "grade": "2", "class": "*", "priority": "1", "isRequired": true, "isPreselected": false, "isManuallySelected": false, "isCodeSelected": false}, {"serial": "2", "stunum": "11*******", "department": "地球科學學系", "grade": "1", "class": "*", "priority": "1", "isRequired": true, "isPreselected": false, "isManuallySelected": false, "isCodeSelected": false}, {"serial": "3", "stunum": "11*******", "department": "地球科學學系", "grade": "1", "class": "*", "priority": "1", "isRequired": true, "isPreselected": false, "isManuallySelected": false, "isCodeSelected": false}, {"serial": "4", "stunum": "11*******", "department": "地球科學學系", "grade": "1", "class": "*", "priority": "1", "isRequired": true, "isPreselected": false, "isManuallySelected": false, "isCodeSelected": false}, {"serial": "5", "stunum": "11*******", "department": "地球科學學系", "grade": "1", "class": "*